verses.roman:
nāraṅga, cholaṅga, ṭābā, kamalā, bīja-pūra
bādāma, chohārā, drākṣā, piṇḍa-kharjura

synonyms: nāraṅga—oranges; cholaṅga—grapefruits; ṭābā—another type of orange; kamalā—tangerines; bīja-pūra—another type of tangerine; bādāma—almonds; chohārā—dried fruit; drākṣā—raisins; piṇḍa-kharjura—dates.
translation: There were also oranges, grapefruit, tangerines, almonds, dried fruit, raisins and dates.
